00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Imagine water boiling and freezing at the same time!

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:10,000
This happens at the triple point, a unique state where ice, liquid, and vapor coexist perfectly.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:14,000
At about 273.16 Kelvin and 611.657 Pascals, this equilibrium occurs.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,200
Sounds wild, right?

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,600
This isn’t just a kitchen trick.

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:21,200
It’s grounded in standard thermodynamics and backed by science.

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:26,000
This fascinating phenomenon showcases nature’s complexity and the beauty of phase transitions.

